ithout explicit permission. The display of third-party trademarks and trade names on this site does not necessarily indicate any affiliation or the endorsement of PCMag. If you click an affiliate link and buy a product or service, we may be paid a fee by that merchant.\\n    \\n\\nInternational Editions:\\n\\n\\nPCMag USA\\nUnited Kingdom\\nAustralia\\nGreece\\nIsrael\\nMiddle East\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\n        \"type\": \"Document\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"lc\": 1,\n      \"type\": \"constructor\",\n      \"id\": [\n        \"langchain\",\n        \"schema\",\n        \"document\",\n        \"Document\"\n      ],\n      \"kwargs\": {\n        \"metadata\": {\n          \"source\": \"https://www.uploadvr.com/meta-hud-glasses-wont-be-ray-bans/\",\n          \"title\": \"Meta's HUD Glasses Reportedly Won't Be Ray-Ban Branded\",\n          \"description\": \"Meta's HUD glasses, coming next year, reportedly won't be Ray-Ban branded or styled after EssilorLuxottica \\\"balked\\\" at the thickness of the frame.\",\n          \"language\": \"en\"\n        },\n        \"page_content\": \"\\n\\n\\n\\nMeta's HUD Glasses Reportedly Won't Be Ray-Ban Branded\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSkip to content\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSearch\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\nSign In\\nSupport Us\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nReviews\\n\\n\\nBest of VR\\n\\n\\nPodcasts\\n\\n\\nShowcase\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nGlasses & AR Tech\\n\\nMeta's HUD Glasses Reportedly Won't Be Ray-Ban Branded As Luxottica \\u201cBalked\\u201d At The Thickness\\n\\n\\n,\\u00a0\\n\\u00a0&\\u00a0\\nDavid Heaney\\n \\n    Today\\n \\n\\n\\n\\nShare to Reddit\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nShare to Twitter\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nShare to Facebook\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nShare to WhatsApp\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\nMark Zuckerberg seen with multiple glasses prototypes and a clear Quest Pro back in February.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nMeta's smart glasses with a HUD, releasing next year, won't be Ray-Ban branded or styled, The Information reports.The existing Ray-Ban Meta Glasses let you capture hands-free first-person photos and videos, take calls, listen to music or podcasts, and livestream your view to a Messenger call, WhatsApp call, or Instagram story. In the US & Canada the other headline feature is Meta AI, a conversational assistant you can talk to by saying \\\"Hey Meta\\\". Mark Zuckerberg has said on multiple occasions that Meta has seen huge demand for Ray-Ban Meta Glasses and the company is selling them as fast as it can make them.What the current glasses lack though is any kind of display, and that's what Meta's next glasses, codenamed Hypernova, are set to bring. The existence of Hypernova was first reported in early 2023 by The Verge's Alex Heath, who seemed to describe it as a new generation of the Ray-Ban glasses. Heath's report described Hypernova as having a heads-up display (HUD) to show notifications, scan QR codes, and translate real-world text in real-time. To be clear: this won't be AR, it will be a small fixed contextual display.In a new report today, The Information's Wayne Ma and Kalley Huang say Hypernova won't be a partnership with EssilorLuxottica, the eyewear company that owns Ray-Ban, because the company \\\"balked at the design\\\".To project an image into your eye and deliver the HUD, the report says, Hypernova will have \\\"a thick frame that current and former Meta employees say is likely to turn off consumers\\\", and this was a dealbreaker for EssilorLuxottica.That projection system also brings the weight up to around 70 grams, the report says, compared to the roughly 50 grams for the Ray-Ban Meta glasses and 30 grams of traditional glasses.Separately, The Financial Times and The Wall Street Journal report Meta is exploring a multibillion-euro investment in EssilorLuxottica, which could help it wield influence in the company's decision making on future smart glasses.Neural Wristband?What the new report doesn't mention is whether Hypernova is still set to come with Meta's long-in-development neural wristband input device as Alex Heath's 2023 report suggested it would.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n0:00\\n\\n                            /0:22\\n\\n\\n1\\u00d7\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nInterestingly, Mark Zuckerberg was seen demoing the neural wristband to the founder and chairman of Luxottica back in 2022, suggesting the companies may have been partnered on Hypernova at some point in the past.The wristband originates from Facebook's 2019 acquisition of New York startup CTRL Labs, and its CEO and co-founder still works on the project at Meta. It works by sensing muscle activation in your wrist using a technique called electromyography (EMG) to track the movement of your fingers. Theoretically this could have zero or even negative latency, perfect accuracy, work regardless of lighting conditions, and not be subject to occlusion.Zuckerberg: Neural Wristband To Ship In \\u2018Next Few Years\\u2019Mark Zuckerberg says Meta\\u2019s finger-tracking neural wristband for AR/VR input will ship \\u201cin the next few years\\u201d. Explanation here:UploadVRDavid HeaneyOn a talk show in February Zuckerberg said the wristband will ship as a product in \\\"in the next few years\\\", which could suggest it will be bundled with Hypernova as originally planned. Alternatively, Meta could be banking on the rapid advancement of conversational AI as a cheaper input method and push the neural wristband out for future hardware.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nGlasses & AR Tech\\n\\nAndroid Watch App WowMouse Offers Hand Pointing & Gestures Without Camera Tracking\\n\\n\\n,\\u00a0\\n\\u00a0&\\u00a0\\nIan Hamilton\\n\\n\\n        19 June\\n \\n\\n\\n\\nWeekly Newsletter\\nGet a weekly summary of the most important VR and AR news.\\n\\n\\nCheck your inbox to confirm!(it might also be in your spam folder)\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nGlasses & AR Tech\\n\\nUltraleap Demos Meta's Ray-Ban Glasses With All-Day Hand Tracking Sensor Added\\n\\n\\n,\\u00a0\\n\\u00a0&\\u00a0\\nIan Hamilton\\n\\n\\n        19 June\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nGlasses & AR Tech\\n\\nXreal Beam Pro Is A $200 Phone-Like Device To Power Xreal Glasses & Capture 3D Content\\n\\n\\n,\\u00a0\\n\\u00a0&\\u00a0\\nDavid Heaney\\n\\n\\n        18 June\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nCommunity Discussion\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nWeekly Newsletter\\n\\n\\nSign up to get a weekly summary of the most important VR and AR news, straight to your inbox.\\n\\n\\nCheck your inbox to confirm!(it might also be in your spam folder)\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\nMore Glasses & AR Tech\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n        19 June\\n\\n\\nAndroid Watch App WowMouse Offers Hand Pointing & Gestures Without Camera Tracking\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n        19 June\\n\\n\\nUltraleap Demos Meta's Ray-Ban Glasses With All-Day Hand Tracking Sensor Added\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n        18 June\\n\\n\\nXreal Beam Pro Is A $200 Phone-Like Device To Power Xreal Glasses & Capture 3D Content\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n        30 May\\n\\n\\nMagic Leap And Google Announce AR Partnership\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\nLatest Articles\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nIndustry News\\n\\nMeta's AR/VR Hardware Teams Must Reportedly Cut Spending By 20%\\n\\n\\n,\\u00a0\\n\\u00a0&\\u00a0\\nDavid Heaney\\n\\n\\n    Today\\n \\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nHeadsets & Tech\\n\\nMeta Reportedly Plans Two Quest 4 Variants For 2026, Then Quest Pro 2 In 2027\\n\\n\\n,\\u00a0\\n\\u00a0&\\u00a0\\nDavid Heaney\\n\\n\\n    Today\\n \\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nHeadsets & Tech\\n\\nbHaptics TactSuit Now Works In Some PlayStation VR2 Games, Including Breachers\\n\\n\\n,\\u00a0\\n\\u00a0&\\u00a0\\nDavid Heaney\\n